Editable prompts/skills — Stage B: authoring API (read/write/reload)

REST API to edit author prompts + skills from the dashboard with hot-reload,
no redeploy. Writes go to the persisted workspace overlay (Stage A).

- gateway/src/api/routes/authoring.routes.ts (new mounter, wired in routes.ts):
  - GET /api/prompts, PUT /api/prompts/:file  (SOUL/STYLE-GUIDE/VOICE-PROFILE/
    PERSONALITY; writes workspace/soul/, then soul.reload()).
  - GET /api/skills (catalog incl. source), GET /api/skills/:name (full content,
    usable as an edit template).
  - PUT /api/skills/:name  (writes workspace/skills/<category>/<name>/SKILL.md,
    overriding a built-in by name; validates name/category/frontmatter; then
    skills.reload()).
  - DELETE /api/skills/:name  (workspace skills only — built-ins read-only;
    deleting one that shadowed a built-in reverts to the built-in).
  - POST /api/authoring/reload  (re-read prompts + skills from disk).
  All writes path-whitelisted via safePath; internal prompt files, no
  confirmation gate.
- tests/api/api-test.sh: +11 checks (list/read + write/delete validation;
  read-only built-ins; reload). Plus a live e2e verified create / override /
  delete-to-revert / delete, with workspace cleanup.
- docs/TODO.md: Stage B marked done; Stage C (dashboard viewer→editor) remains.

